725672f-a.text:

725676f-d.title: Queens: 82nd Street - 30th Avenue
725676f-d.text:
82nnd Street, east side, between Thirtieth and Thirty-first
Avenues, showing in a set of 4 views the Hazard-Duryea farmhouse.
Some owners of this property were Judge James Hazard in 1740-1765;
John Duryea, 1852; Mrs. E. Duryea, 1873; Duryea 1891; and L. Duryea
in 1896. The house was rased in May 1927. This house has 30 inch
shingies and half doors.
April 1923.
Views 1, 2, 3 and 4.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725674f-a.title: Queens: 82nd Street - 30th Avenue
725674f-a.text:
82nd Street, east side, between 30th and 31st Aves., showipg the
Duryea-Hasard house. It was erected about 1750 by Judge James Sasard
of the Court of Common Pleas. It was subsequently purchased by the
Duryea family and remained in the family until it was demolished prior
to 1927. If standing in 1938 it would occupy 1ot four in block 151.
This is a set of two views.
Arthur White.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
